full_text.4:
Anyway. It's been fun. To all the people who I only know via Twitter, take care. 

My IG is /BurgessAnthem (my original handle here, too).
full_text.5: 3 years ago, when I got married, I took an entire week off Twitter to hang with my groomsmen and enjoy real life. It was probably the blissful happiness of the occasion, but sans Twitter I was insanely stress free. And my therapist says it's bad for me.
full_text.6: Anyway, these are just a couple reasons why Twitter was good. I met legitimately awesome people. I got out of my comfort zone. It is DEFINITELY a hellsite. But not to get too cliche, it was our hellsite.
full_text.7: I think Twitter made me a better writer in that way.
full_text.8: As a writer, Twitter was fun. Forcing you to say something in 140 characters, especially difficult in 09 when you couldn't thread. I've said (to myself at least (crazy person)) that I often think in 140 characters. I'm constantly writing pithy dumb shit in my brain.
full_text.9: In college, I used Twitter to flirt with a girl I met at /another/ journalism conference. We DM'ed for a long while before actually texting like normal people.
full_text.10: I joined Twitter in 2009 at a college journalism conference because everyone was tweeting where the parties were at the hotel. My first tweet was something like "where the party at?" with the conference's hashtag.
